assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: Tekken Corporation engages in the construction business in Japan and internationally. The company constructs infrastructure projects, including roads, tunnels, bridges, water supply and sewerage facilities, and river revetments; railroad infrastructure, such as railroad viaducts, bridges, tunnels, embankments, and station platforms, as well as stations, station buildings, and railyards; and commercial buildings, such as condominiums, schools, and medical and welfare facilities. It also engages in real estate development business, as well as building renovations, and consulting services. In addition, the company engages in the agriculture, renewable energy, biomass plastics, PFI projects, and other field businesses. Tekken Corporation was incorporated in 1944 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan.
